1. GALE WARNING: SOUTH TO SOUTHEAST WINDS WILL INCREASE TO GALE FORCE DURING
TODAY ON ALL IRISH COASTAL WATERS AND ON THE IRISH SEA.
SMALL CRAFT WARNING: SEE GALE.
2. METEOROLOGICAL SITUATION AT 4AM: A WEAK RIDGE OVER IRELAND WILL BE REPLACED
BY A STRENGTHENING SOUTHERLY AIRFLOW TODAY AS AN ACTIVE FRONTAL SYSTEM MOVES
IN OVER THE COUNTRY FROM THE ATLANTIC CLEARING INTO THE IRISH SEA TONIGHT.
3. FORECAST FOR COASTS FROM MALIN HEAD TO HOWTH HEAD TO ROCHES POINT AND
FOR THE IRISH SEA:
WIND: VARIABLE FORCE 2 TO 4 BECOMING SOUTH TO SOUTHEAST FORCE 3 OR 4 THIS
MORNING AND INCREASING FORCE 6 OR 7 AND GUSTY IN THE AFTERNOON AND EVENING
OCCASIONALLY REACHING GALE FORCE 8 AND VEERING NORTHWEST OVERNIGHT.
FORECAST FOR COASTS FROM ROCHES POINT TO SLYNE HEAD TO MALIN HEAD:
WIND: SOUTH TO SOUTHWEST FORCE 3 OR 4 INCREASING SOUTH TO SOUTHEAST FORCE
7 OR GALE FORCE 8 VEERING NORTHWEST LATER IN THE DAY AND MODERATING FORCE
5 TO 7 BACKING WESTERLY TONIGHT.
WEATHER FOR ALL SEA AREAS: HEAVY RAIN SPREADING NORTHEASTWARDS TODAY AND
EARLY TONIGHT WITH SHOWERS TO FOLLOW.
VISIBILITY FOR ALL SEA AREAS: MODERATE OR POOR IN RAIN OR SHOWERS.
4. OUTLOOK FOR A FURTHER 24 HOURS UNTIL 0600 FRIDAY 8TH JANUARY 2016:
STRONG TO GALE FORCE WESTERLY WINDS FOR A TIME LATER BECOMING MODERATE
VARIABLE IN THE NORTH AND STRONG WEST TO SOUTHWEST ELSEWHERE. SQUALLY SHOWERS
